lmn-gpo (1.2.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * New pack 18-point-and-print: allow standard users (students) to install printer
    drivers from the trusted print server(s) via Point and Print. Patched Windows 11
    otherwise blocks this after the PrintNightmare hardening (CVE-2021-34527), so the
    printers that linuxmuster/sophomorix already connects fail with "administrator
    required". Registry-only, opt-in (pointandprint_enabled); the trusted-server list is
    auto-detected (server NetBIOS name + FQDN + IP) plus printservers_extra. The printer
    connection itself is left to linuxmuster/sophomorix.
  * env: expose the server's machine NetBIOS name (server_netbios) so the trusted list
    matches how sophomorix connects (\\SERVER\..).
  * lmn-gpo-check.ps1: add a Point and Print client check section.

 -- Kevin Stenzel <kevin@ks98.de>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0000

lmn-gpo (1.1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Rename for consistency with the lmn-gpo command: the Python module is now
    lmn_gpo (was lmgpo), the source launcher is lmn-gpo-cli, and the client check
    script is lmn-gpo-check.ps1.
  * Config directory moved to /etc/linuxmuster/lmn-gpo/ (was /etc/linuxmuster/lmgpo/).
    An existing site.yaml at the old path is migrated on install and is still read
    from a source checkout as a fallback — no settings are lost. Once the migration
    copy has succeeded, the old /etc/linuxmuster/lmgpo/site.yaml is removed.

 -- Kevin Stenzel <kevin@ks98.de>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 13:00:00 +0000

lmn-gpo (1.0.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package of the linuxmuster-gpo-template toolkit.
  * Installs the lmn-gpo CLI (/usr/bin/lmn-gpo), the lmgpo Python module and the
    read-only policy data under /usr/share/lmn-gpo (catalog, scripts, lib).
  * Reads its configuration from /etc/linuxmuster/lmgpo/site.yaml; an existing
    site.yaml from a previous source checkout is migrated on install.

 -- Kevin Stenzel <kevin@ks98.de>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000
